.TH FORWARDER 1
.SH NAME
forwarder \- simple port forwarding agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B svc/forwarder
[
.B -d
]
[
.B -F
]
[
.B -m
mode
]
source destination
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Forwarder
is a port forwarding agent meant
to work across network filesystems. It takes the
.IR source
mount, the
.IR destination
mount, and forwards
.IR src
to
.IR dst
according to the configuration.
.PP
Options:
.TP
.B -d
Enable debug messages.
.TP
.B -F
Run in foreground, not releasing the terminal.
.TP
.BI -m " mode"
(TODO) Use the operation in the specified mode. In the future,
local and remote mounts will be supported.
.SH SOURCE
.B /dis/svc/forwarder.b
